postcontent:
MAUSER RIFLE ... 7x57 caliber ... 21 1/2" barrel ... adjustable rear sight has settings for 14 different distances ... front blabe sight has heavy protective wings and adjustment for windage ... left side of stock has custom hardware for sling attachment ... cleaning rod has carry port under the bayonet attachment hardware. 

The left side of the receiver is engraved, "MAUSER-WERKE A.6. OBERNDORF a/N". The top of the receiver is engraved with crossed rifles and, "CHILE ORDEN Y PATRIA MODELO 1935". The left side of the stock is impressed with a circular seal, the number 1935 and the letters 'CaE'. 

This rare item is in exceptional shape and would be a fine addition for a collector. ALL PART NUMBERS MATCH, the gun is absolutely mint. 

This rifle was the last contract that Mauser did before the war. There were only but so many made for the Chilean mounted police. Its really cool that you can still clearly see the markings on the rifle because most of the ones you do see in collectors books have been rubbed off due to there mounting position.

Let me know if you have any questions.

title: For Sale:  $25 muzzle crowning
location: Hampton Roads, VA Beach, Hampton Roads, Virginia
postcontent:
I am offering a $25 re-crowning service for any 22 caliber or 30 caliber firearm (May not work for some 22lr pistols). Crown is an 11 degree target crown and I can also polish the finished crown for free for added protection from moisture and carbon (optional)

Why Re-crown?
The crown is the absolute last thing the bullet touches when leaving the rifle, and it directs the gas as it leaves.  Any imperfection on a barrel crown causes the gasses exiting behind the bullet to push the bullet in a non-straight line, causing tumbling, POI shift, and reduced accuracy.  Re-crowning creates a uniform and smooth surface.  As the bullet leaves the barrel, the gasses exit around the bullet evenly causing minimal impact to the bullet's travel, which causes an increase in precision (small groups) and accuracy (hitting your target).   

Ideal applications:
Military surplus firearms (Mosin Nagant, Mauser, SKS, M1 Garand, AK, M98, etc)
Mass-production firearms (AR15, AR10, AK, etc)
Varmint and hunting rifles
Competition rifles
Target model pistols
Anyone who wants to increase precision
Any firearm with old/worn/damaged muzzle or crown

Doesn't the pilot damage the inside of the barrel?
No, the tool I use has an aluminum pilot that does not move inside the barrel during the process, eliminating any possible damage to the barrel.  Aluminum is too soft to damage the barrel.

Are you an FFL?
No, so you will have to be present when I perform the work which takes LESS THAN 10 MINUTES per barrel.  

Warranty:   
I will stand behind my work 100%.  If I botch your barrel in any way, I will pay for either a replacement barrel or another crowning job at the location of your choosing (in Hampton Roads). 

Payment:
PayPal or cash only.  For PayPal, send payment to REDACTED.  Please call first to schedule date/time.  

Contact info: 
Send an email to REDACTED (yes I am in the USMC) with the gun make, model, and caliber (and qty if applicable).  

About Me:
I am a skilled and technical person who has been building guns and reloading ammunition for over 6 years.  I hold myself to a very high standard and consider my work to reflect that.  I also understand the importance of customer satisfaction. 

Below is a picture of a good crown and a bad crown. Note the pattern showing even gas dispersion around the bullet as it exists the barrel.  That indicates a very good crown.  Even the smallest ding in the crown can significantly reduce accuracy and precision (circled in red).

Note:  I will also cut a barrel to a shorter length for an additional $15.  I cannot guarantee a perfect 90 degree angle because I do not have a lathe.  I will not create an NFA weapon (16" minimum barrel length for rifles).

title: For Sale:  looking to see if anyone is interested in $25 muzzle crowning
location: Hampton Roads, VA Beach, Hampton Roads, Virginia
postcontent:
I am about to purchase a high quality barrel reamer from Manson Reaming that can do 11 degree target crowns for any 22 caliber or 30 caliber guns (including 22lr, .223/5.56, .308/7.62, 30-06, and many more).  I can also include popular pistol calibers such as 9mm, 40 caliber, and 45 caliber, but the benefits are much higher on rifles.  I want to know if anyone is interested in this service for $25 (or less).  Many professionals will charge more than 3 times this much and they have inferior or dull cutters which can do more damage than good.  

Why Re-crown?
The crown is the absolute last thing the bullet touches when leaving the rifle, and it directs the gas as it leaves.  Any imperfection on a barrel crown causes the gasses exiting behind the bullet to push the bullet in a non-straight line, causing tumbling, POI shift, and reduced accuracy.  Re-crowning creates a uniform and smooth surface.  As the bullet leaves the barrel, the gasses exit around the bullet evenly causing minimal impact to the bullet's travel, which causes an increase in precision (small groups) and accuracy (hitting your target).  Polishing the final crown surface is optional (and free).  

Ideal applications:
Military surplus firearms (think Mosin Nagant)
Any mass-production firearm
Suppressor use (assuming your threading is concentric to the bore) 
Anyone who wants to increase precision and accuracy

Doesn't the pilot damage the inside of the barrel?
No, the tool I am buying has a pilot that does not move inside the barrel during the process, eliminating any possible damage to the barrel.  

Are you an FFL?
No, so you will have to be present when I perform the work which takes LESS THAN 10 MINUTES per barrel.  

Cost: 
Depends on demand.  More barrels = lower price.  
10 barrels @ $25 ea
15 barrels @ $20 ea
20 barrels @ $15 ea
25+ barrels @ $10 ea

Warranty:   
I will stand behind my work 100%.  If I botch your barrel in any way, I will pay for either a replacement barrel or another crowning job at the location of your choosing (in Hampton Roads). 

Payment:
paypal or cash only.  For paypal, contact me first to see how much (based on the number of requests)

Contact info: 
Send an email to devildog4045@gmail.com (yes I am in the USMC) with the gun make, model, and caliber (and qty if applicable).  

About Me:
I have been in the USMC for over 11 years and have 2 combat deployments.  I love guns, reloading, shooting, and customizing guns, but I am not a professional gunsmith.  I am a skilled and technical person who has been doing my own custom gun building and reloading for over 5 years for myself and my family.  I hold myself to a very high standard and consider my work to reflect that.  I also understand the importance of customer satisfaction. 

Below is a picture of a good crown and a bad crown. Note the pattern showing even gas dispersion around the bullet as it exists the barrel.  That indicates a very good crown.  Even the smallest ding in the crown can reduce accuracy and precision (circled in red)

I am selling an Enfield NO4 MKI chambered for 303 British. 85% bluing, sharp bore and with excellent accuracy. I was able to score 30 shots on paper at 300 yards open sights.

150 rounds of Prvi Partizan FMJ were fired, so I will  include the casings will be included; they are non-corrosive and re-loadable along with 5 stripper clips. Included is also the long screw driver used to disassemble the buttstock from the rifle.

A lil' about the rifle:

The rifle was build in 1943 and refinished in 1946. The odd thing about this rifle is that it comes with the Jungle adjustable flip sights (Adjustable to of 800 meters), both the peep sight and the front blade sight were painted
white by its serviceman for easier target acquisition, the leather sling that comes with the rifle displays the message "Mah Hell" scratched onto it.

The wood is in excellent shape, with a dry part between the trigger guard and the buttstock, other than that it is in excellent condition. I bought a grooved handguard with the original included as well.

It has some interesting markings and I am willing to take some pics from them per request.

Price is negotiable, no trades.
